
SAGA Tutorial Structure
-----------------------

180 min total
  - 150 min for slides, as below
  -  30 min for delays, hands-on-tutorial, questions, feedback

-----------------------

(20 min)  Introduction    
          [introduction.pdf]


(60 min)  API walkthrough + tutorial examples
          [api.pdf]

          - standardization overview
          - API structure
          - API walkthrough         (look & feel, functional packages)
          - software components
            - C++ API               (saga-core)
            - middlewars bindings   (saga-adaptor-xyz)
            - language bindings     (saga-binding-python)
            - tools etc
              - command line tools
              - make system support
              - installation tools
              - configuration files (*.ini)
              - environment settings, runtime behaviour, debugging, etc


(30 min)  Installation and Deployments 
          [installation.pdf]

          - code packages and dependencies
          - configure ; make ; make install
          - mephisto
          - notable deployments


(30 min)  adaptor development
          [adaptors.pdf]

          - API vs. CPI
          - adaptor generator
          - complete exmaple


(10 min)  Closing
          [conclusion.pdf]
         
          - overview over active SAGA projects
          - contact points, references, feedback

